SIMPLE: failing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Failing
<hw>Fail"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A failing short; a
becoming deficient; failure; deficiency; imperfection; weakness; lapse;
fault; infirmity; <as>as, a mental <ex>failing</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And ever in her mind she cast about⟦br⟧
For that unnoticed <qex>failing</qex> in herself.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of becoming insolvent of bankrupt.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Fault</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Faille</ent>⟦br⟧
